snippet.textDisplay: Okay let me explain to you why the term haters is overused and why some people will never consider him the GOAT. I speak for the other 31 teams fanbases. 1. The dude has no major special talents like Lamar Jacksons/Michael vicks running, Patrick mahomes/Dan Marino's arm talent, or superb body strength like Andrew luck/deshaun Watson. Or overall ability like Aaron Rodgers. This dude came into the combine as someone who looked more like a UPS driver than a hall of fame quarterback. 2. Bill belichick has been grooming players for decades before the Patriots had even looked in the general direction of this man. Bill has had his hand in some of the greatest teams of their time and maybe even of all time. Anyone who thinks Brady is more responsible for this dynasty than Bill needs to be put in a straight jacket and sent off to do coloring books for the rest of their life. 3. If we want to get scientific here, let's point out some things. The amazing amount of things that happened in the timeline for this man to get where he got, was astronomical. We call this the butterfly effect, what if bledsoe never gets hurt? What if he plays another two years? What if Brady is drafted one spot differently? What if he's never drafted?  A different head coach? What if tuck rule doesn't happen? What if Randy Moss never comes to the Patriots? What if vinatieri misses? What if beastmode gets the ball? What if the falcons hold one drive? What if Dee Ford isn't offsides? The course of history and time itself gave this man the luckiest breaks. These split second actions made him into Tom Brady rather than Jim Kelly, or Ryan Leaf, or maybe just some guy down the road. 4. Now finally I can scream from the mountain tops something that Patriots fans or any other brown noser cant take away from the fans that feel the same way I do. Tom Brady will never be considered the goat for those reasons I've listed and the final reason I'm about to say. THE AMOUNT OF SKETCH BEHIND THIS MANS CAREER IS MORE THAN ANY OTHER PLAYER EVER. see when people cheat and don't win, nobody cares, but when you get caught once and have a whole hallway dedicated to the trophies and the honors. They're not trophies anymore, they're lies. False gods who proclaim that trusting them is in our best interest. Immortals who want our worship while they have crossed fingers behind their backs. It disgust me how Patriots fans and the apologist can turn a blind eye and call us heretics in the name of the game itself, whilst they chant "six rings" and "goat" looking to silence our grievance. I say no more, I spit on your relic, I bite my thumb to your proclamation, and I will NEVER CALL TOM BRADY THE GOAT.
